blumi — third-party notices
===========================

blumi bundles a curated snapshot of agent **skills** (SKILL.md files) from the
following third-party projects, embedded into the binary and written to
~/.blumi/skills on first run. Each is used under its respective permissive
license (MIT or BSD-3-Clause); full license texts are in
crates/blumi-skills/bundled/licenses/.

- obra/superpowers            (prefix: sp-)       — MIT, Copyright (c) 2025 Jesse Vincent
  https://github.com/obra/superpowers
- leonxlnx/taste-skill        (prefix: taste-)    — MIT, Copyright (c) 2026 Leonxlnx
  https://github.com/leonxlnx/taste-skill
- jeffallan/claude-skills     (prefix: cs-)       — MIT, Copyright (c) 2025 Jeff Allan
  https://github.com/jeffallan/claude-skills
- udapy/rust-agentic-skills   (prefix: ras-)      — MIT, Copyright (c) 2025 Rust Agentic Skills Contributors
  https://github.com/udapy/rust-agentic-skills
- flutter/skills              (prefix: flutter-)  — BSD-3-Clause, Copyright 2026 The Flutter Authors
  https://github.com/flutter/skills
- dart-lang/skills            (prefix: dart-)     — BSD-3-Clause, Copyright the Dart project authors
  https://github.com/dart-lang/skills
- workos/auth.md              (skill: workos-auth) — MIT, Copyright (c) 2026 WorkOS
  https://github.com/workos/auth.md
  (AUTH.md is vendored as the `workos-auth` SKILL.md; its agent-services /
  agent-providers implementation guides are kept under references/.)

Skill folders are namespaced by the prefixes above to avoid collisions (the
flutter/dart skills already carry their `flutter-`/`dart-` topic prefix upstream,
so they are vendored as-is). To refresh the vendored snapshot, run
scripts/vendor-skills.sh.

The default MCP server set and catalog reference the Model Context Protocol
reference servers (modelcontextprotocol/servers) and entries curated from
punkpeye/awesome-mcp-servers; those run as separate processes via npx/uvx and
are not redistributed here.
